{"body": "The percentage of teams writing actual acceptance tests is not very large, as far as I can tell. I certainly don't think that the average Rails team is writing them. If we rename integration/functional/system tests to \"acceptance\" tests, we recreate exactly the problem that this PR is designed to solve. Instead of confusing Rails programmers about what \"unit\" means, we'll confuse them about what \"acceptance\" means.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9277060", "created_at": "2012-10-09T20:10:15Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7878#issuecomment-9277060", "updated_at": "2012-10-09T20:10:15Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7878, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/garybernhardt", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0f3aad429c4fe35ea2bcffa654995a5e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8bfcbdd65996c417acdfad207838abb9.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0f3aad429c4fe35ea2bcffa654995a5e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "garybernhardt", "type": "User", "id": 45707, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/garybernhardt/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f7febd3543c15100b19a"}, "id": 9277060, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7878"}
